  <h3>Key Results</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Upper A-arm:</strong> Passed all fatigue qualification stages — full 2-year life validated</li>
    <li><strong>Lower A-arm (original design):</strong> Failed at 94% of 2-year life (effective FoS = 1.12)</li>
    <li><strong>Failure mode 1:</strong> Delamination/fiber fracture at puck corners → corrective action: increased ply count from 9 to 12</li>
    <li><strong>Failure mode 2:</strong> M4 bolt tensile failure at FoS 0.6 → corrective action: upsize to M5</li>
    <li><strong>Corrected design:</strong> Increased potting radius + Epocast 1626 + M5 bolts + 12 plies targets FoS >1.5</li>
  </ul>

