  <!-- MANUFACTURING -->
  <h2>Manufacturing</h2>
  <p>The hardpoint manufacturing process is tightly integrated with the monocoque layup schedule:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Plug machining:</strong> Hardpoint locating features transferred to the negative mold</li>
    <li><strong>Mold layup:</strong> Bushings installed in negative mold for hardpoint location</li>
    <li><strong>First cure:</strong> Chassis cured, then hardpoint holes drilled out</li>
    <li><strong>Hardpoint installation:</strong> Carbon pucks positioned, potted with Epocast 1626, final cure</li>
    <li><strong>QA:</strong> 3D-printed fixtures used to verify core ramp geometry (45° taper angle, proper cell collapse)</li>
    <li><strong>DXF files:</strong> All reinforcement plies pre-cut with relief cuts, bagged separately for organized layup</li>
  </ul>

